
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Driver {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  -isSick: boolean
}

class Bus {
  +licencePlate: String
  -isInRepair: boolean
}

class Route {
  +routeNumber: int
}

class Shift {
  +shiftType: String
  +day: Date
}

class Assignment {
  +bus: Bus
  +driver: Driver
  +route: Route
  +shift: Shift
}

' Associations between classes
Driver "1" -- "0..*" Assignment : assignedTo
Bus "1" -- "0..*" Assignment : assignedTo
Route "1" -- "0..*" Assignment : has
Shift "1" -- "0..*" Assignment : has

' Additional notes or constraints
note right of Driver
  Unique ID automatically generated
  Cannot be updated, only added or deleted
  IsSick flag affects scheduling
end note

note right of Bus
  Licence plate up to 10 characters
  Cannot be updated, only added or deleted
  IsInRepair flag affects assignment
end note

note right of Route
  Route number up to 9999
  Assigned buses per day
end note

note right of Shift
  Morning, Afternoon, Night
  Day can be up to a year in advance
end note

note right of Assignment
  Represents a driver assigned to a bus on a route for a shift
  Driver and bus must not be on sick leave or in repair
end note

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Key Elements:
- **Driver**: Tracks name and unique ID. Can be marked as on sick leave.
- **Bus**: Identified by licence plate. Can be marked as in repair.
- **Route**: Identified by a route number (up to 9999).
- **Shift**: Morning, afternoon, or night shift on a specific day.
- **Assignment**: Links a driver, bus, route, and shift.

This diagram supports the requirement that drivers and buses cannot be updated, only added or deleted, and includes logic for handling sick leave and repairs.